comment: Lemma for transfinite recursion. Let ` A ` be the class of "acceptable" functions. The final thing we're interested in is the union of all these acceptable functions. This lemma just changes some bound variables in ` A ` for later use. (Contributed by NM, 9-Apr-1995.)
